main event: Two flying saucer-shaped objects were observed over Washington, Missouri, at approximately 2:30 p.m. on July 25, 1964.
interesting points: The objects were silver in color and appeared to be approximately 20-30 ft. in diameter., The objects traveled at a very high rate of speed and quickly disappeared to the south., The sighting was considered authentic and extremely puzzling by the observers., Only two witnesses confirmed the sighting - Mrs. Linda Jaegers and the Sergeant., Despite being in good viewing range, no photographs were taken.
